descriptionNullable:
### Context

**RESPNUM**- Number generated by the computer during data entry	

**CCGID**- Number generated during batching	

**STRATA**- Time frame of survey	
	1	Weekday Peak (Start of service to 9:00 AM, 3 PM to 7 PM)	
	2	Weekday Off-Peak	
	3	Saturday	
	4	Sunday	

**TRAIN**- Train on which survey was collected	

**TRAINSET**- Type of train	
	B	Bombardier	
	G	Gallery	

**DIR**-	Direction of train on which survey was collected	
	N	North	
	S	South  	

**BIKE**- Car Type	
	Y	Bike Car	
	N	Regular Car	

**CAR**- Car # Surveyed	

**INTDATE**- Interview Date	

**DAY**- Day Surveyed	

**MAIL**	- How survey was received	

	1	Returned to surveyor on train	
	2	Mail in	

**LANG**- Language of survey	
	1	English	
	2	Spanish	

**Q1**- How long have you been riding Caltrain?	
	1	This is my first trip	
	2	Less than 6 months	
	3	6 months to less than one year	
	4	One year to less than two years	
	5	Two years to less than four years	
	6	Four years or more	
	0	Blank/Multiple responses	

**Q2**- About how often did you ride Caltrain?	
	1	6-7 days a week	
	2	5 days a week	
	3	4 days a week	
	4	3 days a week	
	5	2 days a week	
	6	1 day a week	
	7	1 - 3 days a month	
	8	Less than once a month	
	0	Blank/Multiple responses	

**Q3**- How did you pay for your train trip (today)?	
	1	One Way Ticket	
	2	Clipper - Cash Value	
	3	Clipper - Monthly Pass	
	4	Go Pass	
	5	Day Pass	
	6	Mobile App - Day Pass	
	7	Mobile App - One Way	
	8	Other	
	9	LEO/SamTrans/Amtrak employee	
	0	Blank/Multiple responses	

**Q21**- What is your current employment status?
	1	Employed full time
	2	Employed part time
	3	Student
	4	Retired
	5	Unemployed
	6	Other
	7	Disabled
	8	Self-Employed/Consultant/Freelance
	0	Blank/Multiple responses

**Q22**- How well do you speak English?
	4	Very well
	3	Well
	2	Not well
	1	Not at all
	0	Blank/Multiple responses

**Q23**- In your home, is English spoken
	4	Very well
	3	Well
	2	Not well
	1	Not at all
	0	Blank/Multiple responses

**Q26**-  Country 


### Content

What's inside is more than just rows and columns. Make it easy for others to get started by describing how you acquired the data and what time period it represents, too.


### Acknowledgements

We wouldn't be here without the help of others. If you owe any attributions or thanks, include them here along with any citations of past research.


### Inspiration

Your data will be in front of the world's largest data science community. What questions do you want to see answered?
title: CSUS Hacks Caltrain Ratings
subtitle: Predict Caltrain Customer Ratings!
